{% comment %}
  example for template<>section-structure

  💡 This .liquid file This json holds the section/component for what is to be rendered in the template

  look out for 💡🏗️ for test-tweaks on the styling
{% endcomment %}

<style type="text/css">
  .template-404 .title + * {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    color: green;
  }

  @media screen and (min-width: 750px) {
    .template-404 .title + * {
      margin-top: 2rem;
      color: hotpink;
    }
  }
</style>

<div class="template-404 page-width page-margin center notfound-404-page-container">
  {% comment %} default class="template-404 page-width page-margin center" {% endcomment %}
  <p>
    {{ 'templates.404.subtext' | t }}
  </p>
  {% comment %}
    💡🏗️
    I've added a tag and gave it a text from the default locales
    the "emotion" property ("😱😱😱") has just been added by myself

    `| t ` might be the translation filter
    https://shopify.dev/docs/storefronts/themes/architecture/locales/storefront-locale-files
  {% endcomment %}
  <h2>
    {{ 'templates.404.emotion' | t }}
  </h2>

  {% comment %}
    💡🏗️
    you can also add more simple tags like so
    the output of object notation {{ 'templates.404.title' | t }} can be seen before the string "lala"
    🤔 still need to find out where this is exactly coming from ... maybe I should try the object documentation of shopify
  {% endcomment %}
  <h1>
    {{ 'templates.404.title' | t }}

    lala
  </h1>
  {% comment %}
    💡🏗️ new elements can be implemented easily like so:

    the class here has been added to base.css and is called upon here.
  {% endcomment %}
  <iframe
    class="notfound-404-page-animation"
    src="https://giphy.com/embed/UoeaPqYrimha6rdTFV"
    width="480"
    height="271"
    style=""
    frameBorder="0"
    class="giphy-embed"
    allowFullScreen
  ></iframe>
  <p><a href="https://giphy.com/gifs/STARFACE-GmbH-looping-404-starface-UoeaPqYrimha6rdTFV">via GIPHY</a></p>
  <h1 class="title">
    {{ 'templates.404.title' | t }}
    {% comment %}
      changing the content of the h1 tag to any string doesn't change the styling.
       👉🏻 the styling here comes from base.css
    {% endcomment %}
  </h1>
  <a href="{{ routes.all_products_collection_url }}" class="button">
    {{ 'general.continue_shopping' | t }}
  </a>
</div>
